# The data packs are served straight off GitHub Pages, and Pages does NOT
# resolve Git LFS pointers — it would serve the ~130-byte pointer text where
# data.js expects gzip, breaking every version. So the packs stay ordinary
# blobs in the repo; do not put *.gz back under LFS while Pages hosts them.
#
# "binary" (= -diff -merge -text) still matters: core.autocrlf is true in this
# repo, and it keeps the packs from ever being line-ending mangled.
*.gz binary
